cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.AR, cs.NI, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a CUDA-based solution for exploring large graphs using a cluster of GPUs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper focuses on the Breadth First Search algorithm for graph traversal. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of the Kepler architecture and its features. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses techniques to reduce the number of communications among the GPUs. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper presents results on the performance of the code in terms of the number of edges visited per second.
